					<main id="main" class="site-main col-md-9"><h1>RUHS - COVID-19 updates</h1>
<br><p><strong>RU Middle and HS families: Below you will find the most recent updates from Principals Elijah Hawkes and Caty Sutton, Senior Project Coodinator Lisa Floyd, and the Student Services office on our response to the current COVID-19 pandemic:</strong></p>
<p><strong>4/21 - Senior Project Update:  Please read the following update and instructions regarding Senior Project:  <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/14ABUzh0IheVynV3ZUtFsIRiKFy34uM3SpRGEOrvZ3fQ/edit">Senior Project Instructions</a></strong></p>
<p><strong>4/16 - Assessment, Grading, and Q4 Course Completion: <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1EQuoGhRliWdizvbJEX9uGWs9RMa2mLJpFy3t_tXSwkA/edit">Assessment Update 4/16</a></strong></p>
<p><strong>4/6 - Extended and Distance Learning Resources: <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1vMBxgVjXlyQLqEtKvsK7dL-zAO46V06t7Qd8DO7moEc/edit">Distance Learning Update 4/6</a></strong></p>
<p><strong>4/1 - Distance Learning Update:</strong>  <strong><a href="http://orangesouthwest.org/media/Page%20Content%20Images/Distance%20Learning%20Update%204%3A1%3A20.pdf">Distance Learning Update 4:1:20</a></strong></p>
<p><strong>Click here for Teacher Office Hours and Student Schedules: <a href="http://orangesouthwest.org/media/Page%20Content%20Images/Teacher%20Office%20Hours%20%26%20Daily%20Student%20Schedule.pdf">Teacher Office Hours &amp; Daily Student Schedule</a><br></strong><br><strong>Click here for the most recent Student Services Update, including information on course selection for next year:  <a href="http://orangesouthwest.org/media/Page%20Content%20Images/Student%20Services%20Update%204%3A1.pdf">Student Services Update 4:1</a></strong></p>
<p><strong>Seventh &amp; Eighth Grade Families: Our teachers and teams are developing new resources to support students n Remote Learning. Here are two resources for the middle school Math, Science, Social Studies and English classes:</strong></p>
<p><strong><a href="https://sites.google.com/orangesouthwest.org/randolphunionmiddleschool7thgr/weekly-assignments">7th Grade Website</a></strong></p>
<p><strong><a href="https://sites.google.com/orangesouthwest.org/randolph-union-middle-school-8">8th Grade Website</a></strong></p>
<p><strong>Read the Press Release from Gov. Phil Scott here: <a href="https://governor.vermont.gov/press-release/governor-phil-scott-dismisses-schools-person-instruction-remainder-2019-2020-school">VT Schools Will Close for Balance of the Year</a></strong></p>
<p><strong>3/24 - Office hours update: </strong> As part of the district’s efforts to have as many people as possible working remotely, we are going to reduce the hours of operation of the RU Main Office to the hours of 11:00 AM - 1:00 PM each day.  Drop-off, Pick Up: As we did last week, we ask that students and families call ahead or email if they need to pick up or drop off something, such as school supplies, or chromebook.  We will arrange to get what you need.</p>
<p>Call or email Lisa Jacobs or Donna Collette:<br> Donna Collette: <a href="mailto:dcollette@orangesouthwest.org">dcollette@orangesouthwest.org</a> 728-3397<br> Lisa Jacobs: <a href="mailto:ljacobs@orangesouthwest.org">ljacobs@orangesouthwest.org</a> 728-3397</p>
<p>Donna and Lisa will answer the phone between 11 – 1, and will be checking phone messages daily. Response time will vary depending on when the message is left and received.</p>
<p><strong>3/18 - Note from Principal Hawkes:</strong> <a href="http://orangesouthwest.org/media/Page%20Content%20Images/RU%20-%20Extended%20%26%20Distance%20Learning%20Expectations.pdf">RU - Extended &amp; Distance Learning Expectations</a><br>  3/18 - <strong>Note from Kara Merrill and Bev Taft:</strong> <a href="http://orangesouthwest.org/media/Page%20Content%20Images/Note%20from%20RU%20Student%20Services.pdf">Note from RU Student Services</a></p>
<p><strong>RU Middle and HS Chromebook Distribution:</strong> At the middle school and high school level, we are now ready for you to come pick up your student’s assigned chromebook and charger, if you need it.<br> <br>To allow maximum flexibility for you, and ensure we do not have any crowding, we ask that you call to let us know when you would like to come by.  We will make sure that the computer is ready at the appointment time. This can happen between the hours of 11 AM and 1 PM.<br> <br>Pick-up appointments can be made for other items as well. Just call ahead to let us know so we can make arrangements.  Call 802-728-3397 and ask for Lisa Jacobs or Donna Collette.<br> <br>This process will allow us to practice social distancing and to follow other procedures for keeping these exchanges sanitary.<br> <br><strong>Food Distribution Update: New Update as of 3/20</strong></p>
<p>The food distribution team is here to serve all OSSD students.  Students will simply need to provide their name at the time of pick up. <em><strong><span style="color: #ff0000;">Note: Food pick up <span style="text-decoration: underline;">will be available</span> during vacation week, April 20-24.</span></strong></em><br> You may pick up food at any of our locations between the hours of 11 am and 1 pm. (Braintree hours are 11 - noon). Please go to the one nearest your home. Food may be picked up at Braintree Elementary School, Brookfield Elementary School and Randolph Union High School.  The food is for any of the district’s students.</p>
<p>You may also pick up food for students outside your families – many folks have done this type of “carpooling” to save fuel.</p>
<p>This will be a drive through service, so please pay attention to the signs and the staff members on duty.<br> Thank you for your patience as we all work together during this stressful time. If you have any questions regarding the program, please contact:</p>
